no-new-symbol.description:
Description

This rule is aimed at preventing the accidental calling ofSymbolwith thenewoperator.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-new-symbol: "error"*/

var foo = new Symbol('foo');

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-new-symbol: "error"*/

var foo = Symbol('foo');

// Ignores shadowed Symbol.
function bar(Symbol) {
    const baz = new Symbol("baz");
}
